 :sidecar: n. 1. Syn. {slap on the side}. Esp. used of add-ons for the late
and unlamented IBM PCjr. 2. The IBM PC compatibility box that could be bolted
onto the side of an Amiga. Designed and produced by Commodore, it broke all
of the company's own rules. If it worked with any other peripherals, it was
by {magic}.